RRI DEM and River Grid Creator

This grid generator reads DEM, DIR, and ACC ESRI ASCII Grid files and
creates a structured RRI grid with the following cell attributes:

  elevation_c, dir_c, acc_c, width_c, depth_c, height_c,
  landuse_c, GSD_s, GSD_c

River width and depth are generated from drainage area:

  width = Cw * (ACC * dx * dy * 1e-6) ** Sw
  depth = Cd * (ACC * dx * dy * 1e-6) ** Sd

DEM, DIR, and ACC must have identical dimensions, origin, and cell size.
Regeneration resets landuse_c, GSD_s, and GSD_c to 1.

After generating the grid, set the RRI RunType to "Run Only".
To regenerate river geometry, change Cw, Sw, Cd, and Sd in this grid
generator dialog and generate the grid again.
